    pearls: ["Drug withdrawal is THE most important intervention — every additional day of causative drug exposure increases mortality; systematically review all medications started within 8 weeks before symptoms","SCORTEN predicts mortality and should be calculated at BOTH 24 and 72 hours — score ≥3 warrants family discussions about prognosis; score ≥5 predicts >90% mortality","Infection is the leading cause of death in TEN (40-50% of deaths) — maintain high vigilance; prophylactic systemic antibiotics are NOT recommended (promote resistance); treat documented infections aggressively based on cultures","TEN is managed LIKE A BURN: specialized wound care, temperature management (ambient 28-32°C), fluid resuscitation, early enteral nutrition, pain management, infection prevention — burn unit consultation or transfer is ideal","Intact blisters are biological dressings — do NOT debride them; the detached but intact epidermis protects the dermis, reduces fluid loss, decreases pain, and prevents bacterial colonization","Distinguishing TEN from SSSS (staphylococcal scalded skin syndrome): TEN = full-thickness epidermal necrosis (deeper cleavage at dermal-epidermal junction, mucosal involvement, Nikolsky positive, adults); SSSS = superficial cleavage (granular layer, no mucosal involvement, mainly in children <5)","Ocular complications are the most significant LONG-TERM sequelae in TEN survivors — chronic dry eye, symblepharon, corneal scarring, and visual impairment occur in up to 35% of survivors; aggressive early ophthalmologic management (within 24 hours) reduces these complications"],
