      type: "Dysphagia management — liquid consistency modifier",
      action: "Increase the viscosity of liquids to slow bolus transit through the pharynx, giving the patient more time to coordinate the swallowing reflex and close the airway before liquid reaches the laryngeal inlet; reduces aspiration risk by matching liquid thickness to the patient's swallowing ability as determined by SLP evaluation",
