      action: "Replaces thyroid hormone after thyroidectomy (essential for preventing hypothyroidism); in thyroid cancer, dosed to SUPPRESS TSH production — TSH stimulates thyroid cell growth, including any residual cancer cells; degree of suppression tailored to risk: low risk → TSH 0.5-2.0 (minimal suppression), intermediate risk → TSH 0.1-0.5 (moderate), high risk → TSH <0.1 (full suppression)",
      sideEffects: "Over-suppression effects (iatrogenic subclinical/overt hyperthyroidism): tachycardia, palpitations, atrial fibrillation (especially elderly), osteoporosis (accelerated bone turnover), anxiety, insomnia, tremor, weight loss, heat intolerance; under-dosing: hypothyroid symptoms (fatigue, weight gain, cognitive slowing)",
